CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 25, 1956, pg. A27 reads: "Leaving Altar - After their valentine evening wedding, Mr. and Mrs. Edmon Davis are shown leaving the altar at Faith Evangelical Church on Ewart Drive. The bride is the former Dorothy Jackson, daughter of Mr. and Mrs. Horace Jackson, 6628 Deary Street.  The Rev. and Mrs. E.D. Davis, 3722 Frazier Street, are parents of the groom - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of wedding party including groom Edmon Davis and bride Dorothy Jackson Davis, standing in center, posed on altar of Faith Evangelical Church, Ewart Drive
